This Is How We Do It: Laparoscopic Roux-en-Y Gastric Bypass.

Landin M(1), Sudan R(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Surgery, Duke University Medical Center, Durham, North 
Carolina, USA.

Morbid obesity afflicts one third of the population in the United States and 
decreases life expectancy by 5-20 years. Laparoscopic Roux-en-Y gastric bypass 
(LRYGB) has been an established operation for the treatment of morbid obesity 
for nearly three decades. There are several different techniques for performing 
a LRYGB. We describe our circular stapled gastrojejunostomy technique and our 
preoperative and postoperative management of patients.

